OL,6,FAt a trial in July, the court heard
OL,7,Fthat Mr Hibbert received 22 wounds
OL,8,Ffrom shrapnel, and Miss Hibbert
OL,9,Fsuffered a "catastrophic brain injury"
OL,10,Fafter a bolt from the bomb struck her
OL,11,Fin the head ` leading to her being
OL,12,Fpresumed dead at the scene.
OL,14,FMrs Justice Steyn said it was clear
OL,15,Fthat Mr Hall's actions, including
OL,16,F"increasingly intrusive and offensive
OL,17,Fpublications" had alarmed and
OL,18,Fdistressed Mr Hibbert and that
OL,19,Ftracking down Miss Hibbert at her home
OL,20,Fwas an unwarranted interference with
OL,21,Fthe family's right to privacy.
